OL,7,F"Tax fraud is not a victimless crime;
OL,8,Fthe public rely on the revenue
OL,9,Fgenerated by tax to fund essential
OL,10,Fservices. No matter how hard they
OL,11,Ftried to conceal their illicit gains,
OL,12,Four expert investigators were able to
OL,13,Funravel their web of lies."
OL,15,FIan Hackett, Operational Lead, in
OL,16,FHMRC's Fraud Investigation Service,
OL,17,Fsaid: "We have worked closely with
OL,18,FKent Police to dismantle this
OL,19,Fsophisticated and complex fraud.
